  "contentPages" : [ 
  
  "The magnitude of how the ideals of the Terrene Protectorate had an influence on the Aureate Brotherhood and vice versa is yet to be fully grasped; ideas of unity for Glitchkind are commonly adopted by many Protectors at the academy, most of the time without knowing that these ideas trace back to the collaboration between the first Protectors and the last Aureate priests and followers, all during the first hundred years of the Terrene Protectorate.",

"The Aureate Brotherhood precedes the Protectorate by approximately 200 years; not much is known about this era other than that they were formed to study an enigmatic artifact they labeled The Regal Medallion. They travelled to many Glitch kingdoms across the stars, realizing that the Glitch were a fragmented species with kingdoms far away from each other, unaware of each other's existence.",

"At the point they encountered the Protectorate, the Brotherhood was already in the middle of its mission to achieve unity and peace for all Glitch. The Brotherhood was important in the first Hermes missions led by the Astraeus Program, and the increased awareness of the Glitch as a species scattered throughout space is the result of their efforts. Sadly, after years of persecution and the destruction of their major temple, the Brotherhood dissolved, with only the echoes of their ideals surviving nowadays."

  ],
